      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MR TADASHI (6) is in red-hot touch as he shoots for four on the bounce over this track and trip. Gets weight off with the rise in grade and keeps Penza, who has partnered the last two. No reason he can't win again. PHILADELPHIA STORM (3) is yet to strike through this campaign but is knocking on the door. Gets a key booking in Loy and if he can manage to settle him a pair or two closer, he will prove awfully tough to hold out over this trip. COUNTY KILKENNY (1) didn't give his rivals a chance last time at Narrandera in a positive change of tactics when sent forward to lead all the way. Should look to do the same here and keeps the 2kg claimer on. MISS STALWART (4) doesn't have form over this trip but her sectionals suggest she wants it. Watch for her darting home.",
